response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: FizzBuzz Counter\", \"description\": \"Write a function `fizzbuzz_count` that takes an integer `n` as input and returns the count of numbers from 1 to `n` that are divisible by either 3 or 5, but not both. For example, if `n` is 20, the function should return 7 because there are 7 numbers between 1 and 20 that are divisible by either 3 or 5: {3, 5, 6, 9, 10, 12, 15}.\", \"code\": \"\\ndef fizzbuzz_count(n: int) -> int:\\n    count = 0\\n    for i in range(1, n + 1):\\n        if i % 3 == 0 and i % 5 != 0 or i % 3 != 0 and i % 5 == 0:\\n            count += 1\\n    return count\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert fizzbuzz_count(20) == 7\", \"assert fizzbuzz_count(25) == 10\", \"assert fizzbuzz_count(30) == 13\"] }"
